# Intuition
I tried applying LCS by reading the given test cases.

# Approach
We try to find the max ascii value of the LCS and then subtract that from the total ascii values of the two strings which gives us the minimum required value.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Recursion: O(2 ^ min(m, n))
Memoization: O(n * m);
Tabulation: O(n * m);

# Recursion(TLE!!!!)
```
class Solution {
public:
    int f(int m, int n, string s1, string s2) {
        if(m == 0 || n == 0) return 0;

        if(s1[m-1] == s2[n-1]) return 2 * int(s1[m-1]) + f(m-1, n-1, s1, s2);

        return max(f(m-1, n, s1, s2), f(m, n-1, s1, s2));
    }
    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        int m = s1.size();
        int n = s2.size();
        int k = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<m; i++){
            k += int(s1[i]);
        }
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            k += int(s2[i]);
        }
        return k - f(m, n, s1, s2);
    }
};
```
