DP problem 3 steps:
1. Definition
Actually,this is the most important step I think.Define your dp matrix correctly enables you to go further instead of a dead end.
In this problem, we define dp[i][j] as the min sum to make s1[0:i] and s2[0:j] the same.
1. Initialize
set i=0 and j=0 individually.
For i=0, we have to make s1(which is empty string ->"") the same as s2[0:j] , the only way to do this is to delete all chars in s2[0:j]
For j=0,we have to make s1[0:i] the same as s2(which is empty string ->"")  ,  the only way to do this is to delete all chars in s1[0:i]
1. Genearlize
Consider i>=1 & j>=1
If s1[i-1] = s2[j-1] , no deletion needed , so dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1]
else : there are two ways to make s1[0:i] the same as s2[0:j]
		One is to delete s1[i-1] ,based on the condition that s1[0:i-1] and s2[0:j] is already the same.
		The other is to delete s2[j-1],based on the condition that s1[0:i] and s2[0:j-1] is already the same.






```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(s1.size()+1,vector<int>(s2.size()+1,0));
        dp[0][0] = 0;
        for(int i=1;i<=s1.size();i++)
            dp[i][0] = dp[i-1][0] +(int)s1[i-1];
        for(int j=1;j<=s2.size();j++)
            dp[0][j] = dp[0][j-1] + (int)s2[j-1];
        for(int i=1;i<=s1.size();i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=s2.size();j++){
                if(s1[i-1]==s2[j-1])
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1];
                else
                    dp[i][j] = min(dp[i-1][j]+(int)s1[i-1],dp[i][j-1]+(int)s2[j-1]);
            }
        }
        return dp[s1.size()][s2.size()];
    }
};
```

