Intution : 
```
Almost all dp problem revolve around few standard dp problem . if you have grasp of standard dp problem then you can easily solve most the dp Question.

Standard Dynammic Problems :
   1. Knapsack Problem (0/1)
   2. Longest Commom Subsequences
   3. Longest Palindrome.
   4. Subset Problem.
   5. Coin Change Problem
   6. Longest Inncreasing Subsequnces


This problem is almost similar to LCS problem. The only difference b/w is that you have to deal with ASCII numbers
```
Java :
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumDeleteSum(String s1, String s2) {
        int n = s1.length(), m = s2.length();
        int[][] dp = new int[n+1][m+1];

        for(int i = 1;i < m+1;i++) dp[0][i] += (dp[0][i-1] + (int)s2.charAt(i-1));
        for(int i = 1;i < n+1;i++) dp[i][0] += (dp[i-1][0] + (int)s1.charAt(i-1));

        for(int i =1;i < n+1;i++) {
            for(int j = 1;j < m+1;j++) {
                if(s1.charAt(i-1) == s2.charAt(j-1)) dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1];
                else{
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j-1]+(int)s2.charAt(j-1), dp[i-1][j]+(int)s1.charAt(i-1));
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[n][m];
    }
}
```

