# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
In such questions, when they have already given you to find the least value....you need to understand that we need to try out all the cases...

I will be answering this questions

**1) How to start thinking when you know that you have to try out all the cases**

**2) How do we form the cases....**

# **Answer 1)** 

Just break the string..to the **smallest case possible** ..For eg...If the strings would be **s1 = "abcd" s2 = "dbef"**...Now what could be the **smallest case possible..**

S1 has a size of **1** and S2 has a size of **1**

So , let us just consider the first charcter only...

s1 = "a" and s2 = "d"

This is how you approach...

# **Answer 2) **

Now s1 = "a"  and s2 = "d"

We know **they are unequal**, so it is for sure that we need to **delete**..but **what to delete**..we can delete **"a"** also, we can delete **"d"** also and we can delete **"a" and "d"** both....

See...this is **how you framed** the cases..yourself

If we delete **"a" from s1** , the rest string left will be from **i+1 to s1.size()** (i is the index where "a" was there)

If we delete **"d" from s2** , then rest string left will be from **j+1 to s2.size()**(j is the index where "d" was there)

If we delete both of them , **then both the strings will be left from i+1 to s1.size() and j+1 to s2.size()**...

And you need to return the min of all three cases..

How do we write this in code 

```
    int x = s1[i];
    int y = s2[j];

     int p = x+solve(i+1,j,s1,s2,dp);
     int o = y+solve(i,j+1,s1,s2,dp);
    int m = x+y+solve(i+1,j+1,s1,s2,dp);

    return min(p,min(o,m)); 
```

Now, how do we think of the base cases...

Let us say...both the strings **reach their max length possible** 

1) If **i==s1.size() && j==s2.size()**, can you do something after that...The ans is no, **so just return a 0**

Code

```
    if(i==s1.size() && j==s2.size())
    {
        return 0;
    }
```

Now, let us say that your string s1 has reached it's end but s2 has still some charcters left...Now, **can you compare the remaining chacrters of s2** with anything..The ans is no, **so just delete all the remianing characters in string s2**

Code 

```
    if(i==s1.size())
    {
        int sum = 0;
        for(int k=j; k<s2.size(); k++)
        {
            sum+=(s2[k]);
        }
        return sum;
    }
```

Now, apply the same logic **when s2 has reach** it's end **but s1 has come charcters left...**


This is how you do it recursively...

Now, how do we memoize..Two parameters are changing

**1) Index i of string s1**
**2) Index j of string s2**

Just make a **2-d dp array** and store the minimum value in this...

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We will be just iterating both the strings and for each character of string 1 we will traverse all charcters of string s2...so **O(S1.SIZE() * S2.SIZE() )**

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are making a 2-d dp array of size s1.size() * s2.size()..so 
**O(s1.size() * s2.size())**

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int solve(int i,int j,string &s1, string &s2,vector<vector<int>>&dp)
    {

        if(i==s1.size() && j==s2.size())
        {
            return 0;
        }

        if(i==s1.size())
        {
            int sum = 0;
            for(int k=j; k<s2.size(); k++)
            {
                sum+=(s2[k]);
            }
            return sum;
        }

        if(j==s2.size())
        {

            int sum = 0;
            for(int k=i; k<s1.size(); k++)
            {
                sum+=(s1[k]);
            }
            return sum;
        }

        if(dp[i][j]!=-1)
        {
            return dp[i][j];
        }
        if(s1[i]==s2[j])
        {
           long long  int a = solve(i+1,j+1,s1,s2,dp);
            dp[i][j]=a;
            return a;
        }

        int x = s1[i];
        int y = s2[j];

        int p = x+solve(i+1,j,s1,s2,dp);
        int o = y+solve(i,j+1,s1,s2,dp);
        int m = x+y+solve(i+1,j+1,s1,s2,dp);

        dp[i][j] = min(p,min(o,m)); 

        return min(p,min(o,m)); 

    }


    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {


        vector<vector<int>>dp(s1.size()+100,vector<int>(s2.size()+100,-1));
        int ans  = solve(0,0,s1,s2,dp);

        return ans;
    }
};
```

