solutions.content:
This problem is similar as [Edit Distance](https://opaque-ixora-403.notion.site/LeetCode-0072-7f01a69d5a68446ba3664a2656a6159e), the only difference is that we don’t have to replace or insert character, only delete.

# Solution 1 (R)

Consider `cost[i][j]` is minimum cost from `s1[0...i-1]` and `s2[0...j-1]` that make them equal.

So we can divide into two cases

- `s1[i-1]` == `s2[j-1]`
    - no need to delete, `cost[i][j]` = `cost[i-1][j-1]`
- `s1[i-1]` != `s2[j-1]`
    - we can choose to delete `s1[i-1]` or `s2[j-1]`
        - delete `s1[i-1]`
            - `cost[i-1][j]` + `(int)s1[i-1]`
        - delete `s2[j-1]`
            - `cost[i][j-1]` + `(int)s2[j-1]`
    - choose the minimum value to `cost[i][j]`

Also, we need to pre-define `cost[0][j]` and `cost[i][0]` .

- `cost[0][j]` : # of cost to delete `s2[0...j-1]` to make it empty
- `cost[i][0]` : # of cost to delete `s1[0...i-1]` to make it empty

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        int n = s1.size(), m = s2.size();
        vector<vector<int>> cost(n+1, vector<int>(m+1, 0));
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
            cost[i][0] = cost[i-1][0] + (int)s1[i-1];
        }
        for (int j = 1; j <= m; ++j) {
            cost[0][j] = cost[0][j-1] + (int)s2[j-1];
        }
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= m; ++j) {
                if (s1[i-1] == s2[j-1]) {
                    cost[i][j] = cost[i-1][j-1];
                } else {
                    int top = cost[i-1][j]+(int)s1[i-1];
                    int bottom = cost[i][j-1]+(int)s2[j-1];
                    cost[i][j] = top > bottom ? bottom : top;
                }
            }
        }
        return cost[n][m];
    }
};
```

**Time:** `O(mn)`   
**Space:** `O(mn)`    

# Solution 2 (R)

Since `cost[i][j]` is related to its previous index, we can reduce space complexity from `O(mn)` to `O(n)` . `cost[i][0]` and `cost[0][j]` can be simplified as `cost[0]` and `cost[j]` as initial pre-calculation.

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        int n = s1.size(), m = s2.size();
        vector<int> cost(m+1, 0);
        for (int j = 1; j <= m; ++j) {
            cost[j] = cost[j-1] + (int)s2[j-1];
        }
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
            int pre = cost[0], now;
            cost[0] += (int)s1[i-1];
            for (int j = 1; j <= m; ++j) {
                now = cost[j];
                if (s1[i-1] == s2[j-1]) {
                    cost[j] = pre;
                } else {
                    int top = cost[j]+(int)s1[i-1];
                    int bottom = cost[j-1]+(int)s2[j-1];
                    cost[j] = top > bottom ? bottom : top;
                }
                pre = now;
            }
        }
        return cost[m];
    }
};
```

**Time:** `O(mn)`   
**Space:** `O(m)`

