solutions.content:
Matrix update relation :
dp[i][j] = min(s1.charAt(i-1) + dp[i-1][j] , s2.charAt(j-1) + dp[i][j-1] , s1.charAt(i) + s2.charAt(j) + dp[i-1][j-1]) 

Idea is to maintain only two rows (i-1)th and (i)th row as only these are needed to update matrix. This can be easily done by swapping the reference variables of array as shown in following code.
```
class Solution {
    public int minimumDeleteSum(String s1, String s2) {
        int n=s1.length(),m=s2.length();
        int[] a=new int[m+1],b=new int[m+1],temp;
        for(int i=1;i<=m;i++)
            a[i]=a[i-1]+s2.charAt(i-1);

        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
        {
            b[0]=a[0]+s1.charAt(i-1);
            for(int j=1;j<=m;j++)
            {
                if(s1.charAt(i-1)==s2.charAt(j-1))
                    b[j]=a[j-1];
                else
                    b[j]=Math.min(s1.charAt(i-1)+a[j],Math.min(s2.charAt(j-1)+b[j-1],s1.charAt(i-1)+s2.charAt(j-1)+a[j-1]));
            }
						// swapping both arrays
            temp=b;
            b=a;
            a=temp;
        }
        return a[m];
    }
}
```

