# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Simple LCS problem, where we have to sum up the unwanted ASCII.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
If the letters of both the strings match, move forward ignoring both of them, but if not add the minimum of both the possibilities:
1. ith letter of s1 + recursion(i+1,j,s1,s2)
2. jth letter of s2 + recursion(i,j+1,s1,s2)

Remember, if one of the string end first, so the remaining letters in the other string are extra and should be added to the answer, hence accumulate() is used.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n*m)
where, n=size of s1 &
m=size of s2
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(n)
# Code
```
//Recursion-TLE
class Solution {
public:
    int solve(int i,int j,string s1,string s2){
        if(i<0 && j<0)      return 0;
        if(i<0)     return accumulate(s2.begin(),s2.begin()+j+1,0);
        if(j<0)     return accumulate(s1.begin(),s1.begin()+i+1,0);
        int ans=0;
        if(i>=0 && j>=0 && s1[i]==s2[j])    ans=solve(i-1,j-1,s1,s2);
        else    ans+=min(s1[i]+solve(i-1,j,s1,s2),s2[j]+solve(i,j-1,s1,s2));
        return ans;
    }

    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        ios::sync_with_stdio(0);cin.tie(NULL);cout.tie(NULL);
        int sz1=s1.size(),sz2=s2.size();
        return solve(sz1-1,sz2-1,s1,s2);
    }
};
