# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The first thing came to my mind after reading the problem is LCS.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Used the similar approach as used for lcs with a little tweaking.
Instead of calculating the matched character here we are calculating the deleted character.

**Base Cases**
whenever we reach to the end of a string we just delete(if any) all the characters of the other string.

**ith and jth chars have matched**
When the i-th char of s1 matched with the j-th char of s2.just increment both i and j.

**Mismatched chars**
When the chars are different we just delete all the possible cases and return the minimum:
1. delete the ith char of s1
2. delete the jth char of s2
3. delete both the ith and jth char from s1 and s2

We just memoized this recurssion call.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nm)
where n is s1.length() and m is s2.length()

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nm)

# Code
**JAVA**
```
class Solution {

    public int lcs(String s1, String s2, int i, int j,int [][] memo)
    {
        if(i>=s1.length())
        {
            int del=0;
            while(j<s2.length())
                del+=s2.charAt(j++);

            return del;
        }

        if(j>=s2.length())
        {
            int del=0;
            while(i<s1.length())
                del+=s1.charAt(i++);

            return del;
        }

        if(memo[i][j]!=-1)
            return memo[i][j];

        int ans=0;

        if(s1.charAt(i)==s2.charAt(j))
        {
            ans= lcs(s1,s2,i+1,j+1,memo);
        }
        else
        {
            ans= s1.charAt(i)+lcs(s1,s2,i+1,j,memo);

            ans=Math.min(ans,s2.charAt(j)+lcs(s1,s2,i,j+1,memo));
            ans= Math.min(ans,s1.charAt(i)+s2.charAt(j)+lcs(s1,s2,i+1,j+1,memo));
        }

        memo[i][j]=ans;
        return ans;

    }

    public int minimumDeleteSum(String s1, String s2) {

        int [][] memo= new int[s1.length()+1][s2.length()+1];

        for(int i=0;i<=s1.length();i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<=s2.length();j++)
            {
                memo[i][j]=-1;
            }
        }

        return lcs(s1,s2,0,0,memo);
    }
}
